defaultQ515 default&#xa0; 
defaultChair:default Could you just tell us how it is done, very briefly?
defaultJohn Flatleydefault: The Crime Survey is considered to be a gold-standard survey.  We have a random probability sample of the population drawn from Post Office address lists.  A letter goes to that household informing them they have been selected for the survey, and then an interviewer calls at that address and carries out a face-to-face interview in the respondent’s home, capturing their experience of crime over the last 12 months.  Outside the interview, we have a quality-assurance process, 
defaultchecking
default that the information collected has been correctly collected. 
default&#xa0;
defaultQ516 default&#xa0; 
defaultChair:default They are 
defaultface
default-to-face interviews. 
defaultJohn Flatleydefault: Yes.
defaultSir Andrew Dilnotdefault: The response rate is 75%, which is unusually high, and it has been pretty stable.
defaultJohn Flatleydefault: It has been 
defaultconsistently
default at that level for about a decade.
default&#xa0;
