defaultNorman Bakerdefault: You will have to ask them that question, but as I understand it, HMIC undertook further work; the follow-up work was not published, for example, and the conclusion was that it was not as detailed as it might have been.  That has now been corrected by the Home Secretary’s request that HMIC do a full audit.  It is also worth pointing out that while that was going on, the ONS in October 2013 said in their report—and I have the exact quote here—“the system for recording crime in England and Wales by the police is widely recognised by international standards to be one of the best in the world”.  That was just last October, so quite clearly we are all on a learning curve with this.  
