defaultProfessor Silvermandefault: We have to continue along the path we are on.  In other words, we have to wait for HMIC to do their work, and we have to pay close attention to what HMIC says.  By “we” I do not mean the Home Office; I mean everyone in the system.  Attention has to be paid to the assessment report, which is itself part of the process.  For example, if we look in the assessment report, there were issues such as the fact that although users were 
defaulthappy, the documentation of their happiness was not quite sufficient.  That is not a question for the Home Office, but that is the sort of thing that will be done to get us to a position of better assurance.
